 <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">The performance gap between GaN V and silicon is now wide enough that the OEM sourcing decision is no longer "if" but "at what wattage." At 45W and above, GaN V's BOM premium ($1-3/unit) is recovered through freight savings, lower warranty costs, and premium retail positioning. Silicon remains viable only for sub-30W single-port chargers targeting the absolute entry-level price point — a segment with single-digit margins and limited brand differentiation potential.</p>
