 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Gallium Supply Chain Risk & Mitigation</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">China controls over <strong>80% of global gallium production</strong> (USGS data). In July 2023, China imposed export restrictions on gallium and germanium, creating supply chain uncertainty for GaN chip fabrication worldwide.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3"><strong>Mitigation strategies for OEM buyers:</strong></p>
 <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-1 list-disc pl-5 mb-3">
 <li>Diversify across GaN chip vendors (Navitas, Infineon, TI) to reduce single-source risk</li>
 <li>Innoscience's 2024 mass-production of <strong>8-inch GaN-on-Si wafers</strong> cuts device costs 30-40% vs. 6-inch baselines, improving supply stability</li>
 <li>Navitas NV6177 IC (Oct 2024) achieves <strong>98% peak efficiency</strong> — fewer components needed per design</li>
 <li>Lock 6-12 month pricing with your manufacturer to hedge against raw material fluctuation</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Ask your supplier which GaN chip brands they use and whether they maintain buffer stock. A reliable factory like <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">WOWOHCOOL</a> sources from multiple tier-1 vendors to ensure continuity.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">E-Marked Cable Pairing for PD 3.1</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">A common OEM oversight: pairing a high-wattage GaN charger with an inadequate cable. USB PD 3.1 at 240W requires <strong>e-marked USB-C cables rated for 5A / 48V</strong>. Without proper cable pairing, the charger automatically downgrades to 60W (3A default) — negating your product's performance story.</p>
 <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-1 list-disc pl-5 mb-3">
 <li><strong>100W+ chargers</strong>: require 5A e-marked cables (mandatory per USB-IF spec)</li>
 <li><strong>240W EPR chargers</strong>: require 48V-rated EPR cables with extended power range e-marker</li>
 <li><strong>Bundled cable strategy</strong>: include a matched cable in-box to guarantee advertised speeds</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">When sourcing <a href="/products/gan-charger/" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange">GaN chargers for OEM</a>, always specify cable requirements in your RFQ. WOWOHCOOL can supply matched e-marked cables with custom lengths and branding.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/10 border-l-4 border-brandBlue p-6 mt-6 rounded-r-xl">
